      • getPositioningEngine

        public MovinPositioningEngine getPositioningEngine()
                                            throws java.lang.Exception
        Attempts to create a positioning engine. If it succeeds a MovinPositioningEngine is returned, otherwise an exception is thrown. 
         
 try {
     MovinPositioningEngine positioningEngine = movinMap.getPositioningEngine();
     System.out.println("Succesfully gotten MovinPositioningEngine.");
 } catch(Exception ex) {
     System.out.println("An error occurred when getting a MovinPositioningEngine: " + ex.getLocalizedMessage());
 }
        Returns:
        The positioning engine for this map.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - If the positioning engine cannot be created, for example due to too few rights.

      • downloadBeaconData

        public void downloadBeaconData(SuccessListener successListener)
        Attempts to download the beacon data. After downloading the data, the callback (if present) will be invoked. If the data has already been downloaded the callback will immediately be invoked.
        Parameters:
        successListener - A callback to invoke once the downloading has been completed. Can be null.

      • downloadMapData

        public void downloadMapData(SuccessListener successListener)
        Attempts to download the map data. After downloading the map data, the callback (if present) will be invoked. If the data has already been downloaded the callback will immediately be invoked.
        Parameters:
        successListener - A callback to invoke once the downloading has been completed. Can be null.

      • downloadTileManifest

        Parameters:
        successListener - The listener to invoke once the downloading has been completed
